@node Introduction "Introduction to MCommands"

  @{b}@{u}Introduction@{uu}@{ub}

      This package contains 8 CLI commands that fill some gaps left by
  current versions of AmigaDOS. The commands are very compact and follow the
  guidelines for writing Amiga software. These are:

  @{"  BootLog " link BootLog} - records time and reason of reboot;
  @{"ChangeFont" link ChangeFont} - globally replaces @{i}topaz.font @{ui}with a user supplied one;
  @{"ClickStart" link ClickStart} - enables/disables some features of AmigaDOS;
  @{"  Examine " link Examine} - determines type of file using @{"DataTypes" link DataTypes};
  @{"    For   " link For} - allows execution of a command with multiple arguments;
  @{" RXControl" link RXControl} - controls ARexx interpreter;
  @{"   Time   " link Time} - measures command's execution time;
  @{"   Touch  " link Touch} - updates files dates.

      I've been using these commands extensively for several months now, and
  failed to observe any glitches. In fact, three of them are part of my
  regular @{i}Startup-Sequence @{ui}and I didn't notice any strange behaviour. I hope
  you will like them.
      The commands are 'pure' and can be made resident.
@endnode

@node Requirements "Requirements for MCommands"

  @{b}@{u}Requirements@{uu}@{ub}

      @{"  BootLog " link BootLog}, @{"ChangeFont" link ChangeFont}, @{"ClickStart" link ClickStart}, @{"    For   " link For}, @{" RXControl" link RXControl},
  @{"   Touch  " link Touch} and @{"   Time   " link Time} require AmigaDOS 2.04 or higher.
      @{"  Examine " link Examine} requires AmigaDOS 3.0 or higher (@{i}datatypes.library @{ui}V39+).
@endnode

@node Installation "Installation of MCommands"

  @{b}@{u}Installation@{uu}@{ub}

      Use supplied @{i}Installer @{ui}script to copy necessary files. If you intend
  to use @{" RXControl" link RXControl} from Workbench, create an icon for it and insert
  appropriate ToolTypes.
      @{"  BootLog " link BootLog}, @{"ChangeFont" link ChangeFont} and @{"ClickStart" link ClickStart}, can be fully utilized if they
  are called from your @{i}Startup-Sequence @{ui}(note: changing @{i}Startup-Sequence @{ui}is
  not recommended for beginner users).
@endnode

@node History "MCommands History"

  @{b}@{u}History@{uu}@{ub}

      Version 1.0 (21.3.94) - initial release

      Version 1.1 (27.3.94):

    Improvements:
    · even more optimizations;
    · better installation - commands requiring AmigaDOS 3.0 are no longer
      installed under 2.0;
    · slightly improved documentation;
    · all commands now give more informative error messages;
    · directories (or volumes) can now be parameters for @{"  Examine " link Examine 5};
    · @{"  Examine " link Examine} now prints directory names as it scans them;
    · multiple patterns can now be specified in @{"    For   " link For 5} if @{b}DO@{ub} keyword
      appears;
    · @{b}NOQUOTE@{ub} option of @{"    For   " link For 27} prevents parameters from being taken
      into quotes;
    · @{b}DIRS@{ub} option of @{"    For   " link For 26} allows execution of a command for
      directories as well.

    Bug fixes:
    · @{"  Examine " link Examine} could crash when used with badly defined @{"DataTypes" link DataTypes};
    · @{"    For   " link For} treated '%%' literaly, instead of replacing it with '%';
    · @{"   Touch  " link Touch} did not touch directories.

      Version 1.2 (31.1.95):

    Improvements:
    · @{" RXControl" link RXControl} command added;
    · @{"   Time   " link Time} command added;
    · @{b}RETRY@{ub} option added to @{"ClickStart" link ClickStart 56}.

      Version 1.3 (24.8.95):

    Improvements:
    · @{"  BootLog " link BootLog} command added;
    · @{b}QUANTUM@{ub} option added to @{"ClickStart" link ClickStart 62};
    · @{" RXControl" link RXControl} optimization saving more than 300 bytes.

      Version 1.4 (31.8.95):

    Improvements:
    · @{"ClickStart" link ClickStart} has now two versions: one for AmigaDOS 2.04 or higher and
      one for AmigaDOS 3.0 or higher. Version for AmigaDOS 2.04 is shorter,
      but has less options.
    · @{b}BORBLANK@{ub}/@{b}NOBORBLANK@{ub} options added to @{"ClickStart" link ClickStart 49};
    · @{b}BORSPRITES@{ub}/@{b}NOBORSPRITES@{ub} options added to @{"ClickStart" link ClickStart 51};
    · @{b}NOHEADER@{ub} option of @{"   Time   " link Time 15} changed into @{b}NOHEAD@{ub} for compatibility
      with system @{i}List @{ui}command.
@endnode

@node ToDo "To do in MCommands"
@next ToDo

  @{b}@{u}To do@{uu}@{ub}

    Improvements:
    · use other method for recognizing boot reasons in @{"  BootLog " link BootLog};
